-- Ecuador Signs $136 Million Loan Deal With BNDES for Irrigation
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 2013-08-21T22:54:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-21/ecuador-signs-136-million-loan-deal-with-bndes-for-irrigation.html
Ecuador  signed a $136 million loan
contract with Brazil’s state development bank BNDES to help fund
the construction of an irrigation project, the Andean country’s
 Finance Ministry  said today in a statement on Twitter.  The project, located in the Daule-Vinces area of Ecuador’s
coastal Guayas and Los Rios provinces, includes the construction
of about 330 kilometers (205 miles) of canals, the ministry said
in a separate statement sent by e-mail. The ministry didn’t give
details about the terms of the loan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Gill in Quito at 
 ngill4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  